The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for predicting maritime time series data. The use of empirical mode decomposition and ensemble EMD methods for decomposing the original time series data, and the grouping of similar segments to form more proper training datasets for traditional NN methods, suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of neural networks for prediction also suggests that the paper could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper's focus on time series data and the use of decomposition methods suggest that it could also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of data analysis and modeling techniques suggests that it could belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
